    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that they're different frameworks, but in a real debate, one usually holds more weight. if you look at international law and universal human rights, doesn't the asylum argument naturally take precedence over a country's right to control its borders? it feels like the side focusing on human lives is more objectively \"correct\" from a moral standpoint.",
