    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i see, so you're saying the asylum side is basically the \"correct\" moral stance. but what about people who argue that a country's first moral duty is to its own citizens and that uncontrolled borders undermine the social contract? are they just wrong, or is their argument fundamentally invalid compared to the humanitarian one?",
